The paper introduces a novel architecture for deep neural networks that integrates a large addressable memory space into the core functionality of the network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of memory in tasks such as exploration and mapping, which are often associated with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional networks, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) tasks. Finally, the paper discusses the use of memory for data-dependent read/write operations, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
